                    <li><b>Source: </b> From <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1941631045/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&creative=9325&creativeASIN=1941631045">Plant Powered Familes by Dreena Burton (Amazon link)</a>, Double Chocolate Orange Banana Muffins (page 55)</li>
                    
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div id="planning">
                <h2>Planning</h2>
                <p><b>Prep Time:</b> X minutes</p>
                <p><b>Cook Time:</b> 17-19 minutes</p>
                <p><b>Servings:</b> 11-12 muffins <p>
            </div> 

            <div id="preparation">
                <h2>Preparation</h2>
                <h3>Equipment</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Muffin pan</li>
                    <li>Oven</li>

                    
                </ul>
                <h3>Ingredients</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Whole-grain spelt flour, 1 1/2 cups (195 g)</li>
                    <li>Almond flour, 1/2 cup</li>
                    <li>Cocoa powder, 1/4 cup</li>
                    <li>Orange zest, 1 1/2 - 2 tsp</li>
                    <ul>
                        <li>From 1 large or 2 small oranges</li>
                    </ul>
                    <li>Sea salt, 1/4 rounded tsp</li>
                    <li>Baking powder, 1 1/2 tsp</li>
                    <li>Baking soda, 1/4 tsp</li>
                    <li>Pureed overripe banana, 1 cup</li>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Should be about 2 large overripe bananas</li>
                    </ul>
                    <li>Freshly squeezed orange juice, 1/2 cup</li>
                    <li>Maple syrup, 1/2 cup</li>
                    <li>Vanilla extract, 2 tsp</li>
                    <li>Non-dairy mini or regular chocolate chips, 1/4 cup</li>
                    
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div id="cooking">
                <h2>Cooking</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Preheat oven to 350deg</li>
                    <li>In large bowl combine flours, cocoa powder, orange zest, and sea salt</li>
                    <li>Sift in the baking powder and baking soda</li>
                    <li>In a medium bowl, combine pureed banana, orange juice, maple syrup, and vanilla extract - mix all together</li>
                    <li>Fold the wet mixture into the dry mixture</li>
                    <li>Add in chocolate chips</li>
                    <li>Stir until just combined</li>

                    <li>Put in muffin tin</li>
                    <li>Cook for 17-19 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean</li>
                    
                </ol>

            </div>

            <div id="notes">
                <h2>Notes & Tips</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Yum</li>
                    
